div1.p:
Territory of Washington County of Spokane}ss Territory of Washington Plaintiff vs. Wilson D. Coyle Defendant} In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, Spo- kane County, in said Territory
To the Sheriff of Spokane County, Greeting: In the name of the United States, You are hereby commanded to summon T.D. Boggs John E. GilsonJohn Croft Mile Halton to be and appear before the District Court at the Court House, in Cheney, in said County, on the forthwith day of April A.D. 1885, at o'clock M. to there give evi- dence in the above entitled cause on the part of said plaintiff.
Witness the Hon. George Turner, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Washington Territory, and Judge of said Court, and the seal thereof affixed, this 26th day of April A.D. 1885. Kate W. Feauerbach Clerk By R. Strobach Deputy.

Subpoena In the District Court of the Territory of Washington and for the Fourth Judicial District thereof, hold- ing terms at Cheney, in said Territory. Territory Plaintiff vs. Coyle Defendant Returned and filed this 20 day of April A.D. 1885 Clerk By Deputy Sheriff's Fees Serving 6 names at .40 2.40 Mileage 30 miles at .10 3.00 Total, ----$5.40
